eing auto-disabled in native images. Let's craft a single straightforward JSON without markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker image is required, but meaningful devtools coverage needs test-code setup because Spring Boot devtools intentionally disables itself under JUnit/native-image contexts and remote support is opt-in.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For tests that need devtools/restart to be enabled, account for Spring Boot's DevToolsEnablementDeducer: it returns disabled when the stack contains JUnit/Spring Boot test classes and in native image. Exercise enabled restart/autoconfiguration behavior from a helper thread without a JUnit stack, or for RestartApplicationListener-specific behavior set the system property spring.devtools.restart.enabled=true only around that test and restore it afterward. Do not expect devtools-enabled behavior in native-image runs; keep native assertions to APIs that work with devtools disabled. If remote devtools server/client behavior is tested, set a non-empty spring.devtools.remote.secret test property because remote support is opt-in.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Positive enabled-devtools assertions can be false under JUnit or native image even though the library is present.\",\n    \"Restart and classpath file-watching behavior depends on classpath directories and classloader/forking semantics, so tests should avoid brittle full restart cycles unless carefully isolated.\",\n    \"Remote devtools should only be tested locally with a synthetic secret; it should not require an external service or Docker container.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05dab4c79fa62e33016a3eb2ef55e8819489d7b33ed859cdd6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 571, "output": 671, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 2